recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2847/93 of 12 October 1993 establishing a control system applicable to the common fisheries policy (1), and in particular Article 21 (3) thereof,
Whereas Council Regulation (EC) No 3680/93 of 20 December 1993 laying down certain conservation and management measures for fishery resources in the Regulatory Area as defined in the Convention on Future Multilateral Cooperation in the North West  Atlantic Fisheries (2), as amended by Regulation (EC) No 1043/94 (3), provides for Atlantic redfish quotas for 1994;
Whereas, in order to ensure compliance with the provisions relating to the quantitative limitations on catches of stocks subject to quotas, it is necessary for the Commission to fix the date by which catches made by vessels flying the flag of a Member  State are deemed to have exhausted the quota available for Member States;
Whereas, according to the information communicated to the Commission, catches of Atlantic redfish in the waters of NAFO-zone 3M by vessels flying the flag of a Member State or registered in a Member State have reached the quota available for Member  States for 1994,
